OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,FA third of UK adults are currently in
OL,7,Fdebt to their energy firm or worried
OL,8,Fabout falling behind ahead of a 13%
OL,9,Fjump in the price cap from July, a
OL,10,Fsurvey suggests.
OL,12,FThe figure rises to 45% of parents
OL,13,Fwith a child under 18, and 35% of
OL,14,Fdisabled people, the poll for the End
OL,15,FFuel Poverty Coalition found.
OL,17,FAmong those in energy debt, the median
OL,18,Famount owed to an energy supplier was
OL,19,F#750.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,FThe survey also found that 13% of
OL,7,Fthose in debt or worried about missing
OL,8,Fpayments owed money to "someone who
OL,9,Fmakes them feel scared", rising to 24%
OL,10,Fof those who are already in arrears.
OL,12,FSome 32% of those already in energy
OL,13,Fdebt had tried to use less energy over
OL,14,Fthe last 12 months by turning the
OL,15,Fheating off or taking shorter showers,
OL,16,Fwhile 25% said they kept their home
OL,17,Fcolder or warmer than was comfortable
OL,18,Fand 21% had missed rent or mortgage
OL,19,Fpayments.
OL,26,@pD@XOUqD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,FMore than one in five of those in
OL,7,Fenergy debt have needed to skip meals
OL,8,F(21%), while 18% had turned to a food
OL,9,Fbank for support to help cope with
OL,10,Fcosts or arrears.
OL,12,FThe End Fuel Poverty Coalition found
OL,13,Fsupplier support for struggling
OL,14,Fhouseholds had been "mixed", and while
OL,15,F15% of those in arrears had been
OL,16,Freferred to a hardship fund and 15%
OL,17,Fwere on a repayment plan, 13% reported
OL,18,Fhaving no contact from their supplier
OL,19,Fin the past 12 months.
OL,26,@vD@UOUvD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,FFewer than one in five (18%) of those
OL,7,Fin arrears felt they had been treated
OL,8,Ffairly by their supplier and just 8%
OL,9,Fhad been referred to debt advice.
OL,11,FSimon Francis, co-ordinator of the End
OL,12,FFuel Poverty Coalition, said: "These
OL,13,Ffigures lay bare the true cost of
OL,14,Fyears of failure to fix energy debt
OL,15,Fcaused by the sharp increases in bills.
OL,17,F"Millions of people are in debt to
OL,18,Ftheir energy company or worried about
OL,19,Ffalling behind, and yet the price
OL,20,Fshock profiteers are posting billions
OL,21,Fin profits.
OL,26,@tD@_OUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,F"The figures also show that this is a
OL,7,Fcan't pay crisis, not a won't pay one.
OL,8,FVery few people who are in energy debt
OL,9,Fare also in high-earning households.
OL,11,F"Instead, it is ordinary people who
OL,12,Fare skipping meals, visiting food
OL,13,Fbanks and, most alarmingly, resorting
OL,14,Fto risky forms of borrowing just to
OL,15,Fkeep the lights on.
OL,17,F"The energy industry, which has caused
OL,18,Fthis debt through its profiteering,
OL,19,Fmust be made to contribute to clearing
OL,20,Fthis debt mountain."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUyD@AOU|D@TO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,FCentre for Sustainable Energy chief
OL,7,Fexecutive Janine Michael said: "At the
OL,8,FCentre for Sustainable Energy, we
OL,9,Fspeak to people every day who are
OL,10,Fstruggling to keep up with their
OL,11,Fenergy bills ` not because they won't
OL,12,Fpay, but because they can't.
OL,14,F"The long-awaited energy debt relief
OL,15,Fscheme must be brought forward
OL,16,Furgently, and people in debt need
OL,17,Faccess to proper debt advice, not just
OL,18,Fa letter from their supplier.
OL,26,@oD@`OUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,F"But debt relief alone is a sticking
OL,7,Fplaster. The real fix is reducing the
OL,8,Famount of energy households use in the
OL,9,Ffirst place through proper investment
OL,10,Fin energy efficiency and phasing out
OL,11,Fgas. Until we address that, we'll be
OL,12,Fhaving this same conversation next
OL,13,Fwinter."
OL,15,FNed Hammond, deputy director of
OL,16,Fcustomer policy at Energy UK, said:
OL,17,F"Household energy debt has doubled to
OL,18,F#5.5 billion in recent years and
OL,19,Fcontinues to spiral out of control `
OL,20,Fit could reach #7 billion by the end
OL,21,Fof this year.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@HO]yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,F"Too many households genuinely can't
OL,7,Fafford to cover their energy costs,
OL,8,Fbut current regulations also make it
OL,9,Fall too easy for customers to fall
OL,10,Finto arrears, with limited routes to
OL,11,Fget out.
OL,13,F"Suppliers are doing what they can to
OL,14,Fhelp customers and reduce debt levels,
OL,15,Fbut the sheer scale of the problem
OL,16,Fmeans the industry can't fix it alone.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781581669
OL,3,CEnergy debt fears plaguing third of UK
OL,4,Chouseholds ` survey
OL,6,F"To overcome this crisis, a
OL,7,Fcomprehensive debt strategy is
OL,8,Frequired. This should start with the
OL,9,Fswift launch of Ofgem's Debt Relief
OL,10,FScheme."
OL,12,FOpinium surveyed 2,000 UK adults
OL,13,Fbetween May 29 and June 1, of which 9%
OL,14,Fwere behind on payments to their
OL,15,Fenergy supplier and a further 22%
OL,16,F(about 12 million) were worried about
OL,17,Ffalling behind on their energy bills.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/9
